rComments: This guy is the greatest, I want to be like Safstrom when I grow up!
Great teacher. Happy to be in his class

It will be a hard class if you have no background of Nordic countries. And I think it is quite hard for international students(especially for Asian).But the professor is very helpful and nice. It is not hard to get a good score. But it will take you some time to think over the content if you are from a different culture.

The class was not too difficult. There was a lot of reading and you had to write 7 response papers (400 words min) and an 8 page research paper. But Mark is a very fair grader and it is not at all hard to do well in the class. Overall, he's a very enthusiastic teacher who is passionate about Scandinavia.
Good sense of humor. Understanding if you're homework isn't always done. Not strict, but he had no reason to be anyway.

Very enthusiastic and knowledgeable professor. Always willing to help out with questions, and seems to always know the answers off the top of his head. Getting an A from Mark isn't too difficult, as long as you keep up with the reading, which there is a lot of.

I love Mark!  Lots of reading is involved, but most of it is very doable and easy. You can miss a few classes without it affecting your grade at all.  Also, he's an absolute genius in Scandinavian Culture; ask him a question and he'll answer it easily.  Top it all off, he's an easy grader.  Just do the work on time and you'll be fine for the class!

Mark is awesome. You can have a few absences. Have to read a couple fiction books, not bad. He is a little bit adorable. Very easy grader. Interesting material. He knows a lot about what he's teaching and speaks Scandinavian languages fluently. I refuse to take myself off his e-mail list about Scandinavian Club because I liked him so much.

This class was a good amount of reading but it was fairly easy to keep up with. He has a lot of expertise in the subject and is really knowledgeable. He is also a fairly easy grader, as long as you do the work and keep up with the readings you'll be fine!
